					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">This code for the most part works however sometimes the ball will bounce back when its 3 or 4 tiles behind the paddle.</div><br />You're only checking if the position is to the left of the paddle. So it will bounce even if it's too far left.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">| = paddle<br />* = ball<br />* | <br />Ball is to the left of the paddle.<br />*&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; |<br />Ball is to the left of the paddle.<br />*&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />Ball is still to the left of the paddle.<br /></div><br />So all those cases would &quot;collide&quot;. That's why there are two checks for vertical. If you want it to collide horizontally only on the paddle, you'll need a second horizontal check as well.<br /><br />Edit: Wait, I had left and right switched. Edited the post to fix this. Same type of problem, though.</div>

					
