				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Signed number representation is trivial: the highest bit has the negative place value that it would have in unsigned. In an unsigned 8-bit value the high bit has a place value of 128, so in signed 8-bit, it has a place value of -128. Nothing more to it. Conceptually you can think of it as &quot;start at -128 instead of 0 when adding the rest of the bits, allowing us to cover the range from -128 to -1&quot;</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

